I think that's all I have for now, but here's one last question:

Did you learn something new from these questions?
Do other people say that your music taste is very overstimulating, but you find that any other type of music you try to listen to is UNDERstimulating? Boring?

This one's a little niche so feel free to skip it if it doesnt apply to you:

When you're playing a video game, do you feel an overwhelming need to complete every single thing in an area/every quest/get every collectible before you can move on, even if it's no longer fun to do?
Have you ever become dehydrated or very hungry due to executive dysfunction, but were still unable to do anything about it?

On the topic of executive dysfunction, when you experience it (due to paralysis from excessive thoughts or a failure to prioritize tasks), do you find it gets in the way of you caring for your health, hygiene, and environment?
Did you know that people with OCD experience executive dysfunction, and not just people with ADHD?

If you see a disturbing image online, does it stay stuck in your head for days (or even weeks) and cause you extreme distress? To the point where you're unable to be in a state of calm for most of the day?
In reference to the previous question, when this occurs, do you find you have an extremely hard time adapting to the change?
Do you get excessively agitated and annoyed when you have a set plan in your mind, and there's either a setback, issue or change in the plan?
Did you know that under certain circumstances, OCD can qualify as a disability?
Do you tend to overanalyze your interactions with other people and look for conflicts or problems that aren't actually there?

Are you a perfectionist, and believe (even if you're currently trying to escape the mindset) that because you're not the absolute best in the world at a certain skill, that your abilities are not impressive, and it's pointless for you to continue doing it?

Do you tend to get overly anxious and worked up over a small disagreement or conflict (to the point of shutting down or having an episode) because you were left to think over it for too long? This is also an anxiety symptom.
Do you often end up paralyzed and get no work done because you will not allow yourself to do any other task before you finish a specific one?
Do you tend to have difficulties prioritizing tasks and figuring out which one to do first? Seeing the "big picture"?

Did you know that "mental checking" is a thing, and that you don't necessarily have to do *physical* repetitive habits and rituals in order for it to qualify as an OCD symptom? The main example of this is obsessively rehearsing conversations or dissecting ones youve already had

Does this fear often cause you to over-explain yourself in simple conversations so that your words can't be misinterpreted? Over-explaining is also a symptom of ADHD (but for a different reason) and trauma/anxiety (for the same reason as OCD)
Do you have an ever-constant fear of accidentally doing or saying something inappropriate or insensitive? There is a follow-up question to this.
Do you feel restless or depressed when you don't have a thing to pour all your energy into? Like a new show or game? This is also an ADHD symptom
Do you have words, phrases, or even songs that constantly replay in your head, to the point where it interferes with your focus or sleep? This is also an ADHD symptom
Are you overly paranoid about food spoiling and expiration dates, to the point where you wind up throwing out food that's still good?
Do you use sleep either from intrusive thoughts, paranoia, or racing thoughts? If not, don't vote; there's no room for a negative option

@lio_fotia nope 😭😭 people used to get really annoyed at me whenever i covered my ears or made frustrated faces when i was trying to do something and the noise wouldn't let me focus. it leads to a lot of angry outburts

Do you repeatedly rehearse conversations and interactions in your head to the point where it extremely stresses you out and causes you to create an unrealistic version of what will happen? Only for you to realize you were completely overreacting? (also an anxiety symptom)

@lio_fotia yep! people with OCD (and i believe it applies to ADHD and various autism spec disorders as well) can get really overstimulated from noises. for me, it's not any specific noises that set me off, but in what situation those noises are in

Are you sensitive to certain food textures and are unable to eat them? For example, I can't eat most vegetables because I hate the fibrous plant texture, but can eat them fine if they're blended into something else
Do you get extremely annoyed or even angered by noises when you're trying to focus on something? Does it sometimes make you completely shut down?
Have your intrusive thoughts made you afraid to be around other people, whether they're violent, sexual, embarrassing, or socially inappropriate in some way?
(btw this is not a diagnostic test and im not a professional i'm just someone with OCD who is very passionate about the alienation we feel and wants to know what other people with OCD experience)
Do you have so many thoughts racing through your head at once that it often paralyzes you into doing nothing?

Rest of this thread is for people with OCD, or people who suspect that they have ocd 

Do you feel that you're unable to talk about your intrusive thoughts because nobody would be able to understand? Because you're afraid people will think you're violent or a bad person?

Out of curiosity, how many of you are worried you're faking your OCD because you don't have the "common" symptoms often portrayed in media- the only symptoms that society regularly talks about like contamination OCD and organization?
